                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/isla-522" class="program-course-title">
              ISLA 522 Lower Intermediate Arabic (6 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-28436" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Islamic Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Islamic Studies              : The course brings students to the intermediate level, using authentic materials and emphasizing reading and grammar analysis more than the introductory level.  It uses the communicative approach, stressing active participation in class discussions.  It focuses on writing skills and developing vocabulary.  Students should speak Arabic at all times.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014, Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Shokry Gohar, David Nancekivell (Fall)                  Shokry Gohar, David Nancekivell (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Summer</li>
              <li>3 hours and laboratory</li>
              <li>Prerequisite: ISLA 521D1/D2 or equivalent, Placement Test, or permission of instructor.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
